text.section:
A premarital preparation course may be conducted by:
a clinical professional counselor or a clinical marriage and family therapist licensed under Title 17, Subtitle 3A of the Health Occupations Article;
a psychologist licensed under Title 18 of the Health Occupations Article;
a social worker licensed under Title 19 of the Health Occupations Article;
an official representative of a religious institution if the representative has relevant training; or
any other qualified provider approved by a county governing body.
